Title: Object: A Return from an Invasion. or, Napoleone at a Nonplus
Description: Political satire: Napoleon in rags, bemoaning "Jaffa" "Tender Mercies of this Devil and the Consul" "Wilsons Egypt" "Aspernes Loyal Papers" and the fact that "All's gone", is kicked onto the French shore by an English sailor, where he is greeted by the despairing governor of Calais and disapproving French; behind is a building, the "Lion D'Argent", and a hanging sign on another building reads "Le Primiere Consul Quillac". 1803 hand-coloured etching with stipple
Bibliographic references: BM Satires / Catalogue of Political and Personal Satires in the Department of Prints and Drawings in the British Museum (undescribed)
Associated names: Representation of: Napoléon I, Emperor of the French (Napoleon)
